originalText.text: Ken is my go to person when I need a coaching for an audition. He is really smart and quick with breaking down a text and finding ways to help me own the material and make it fun to do! When I can find the fun doing a scene, monologue or song, the fear and thinking too much slips away and I can really dig in and play. When I am playing in the audition room or on my video submission (and not trying to "do it right") I come alive and do my best. Thanks, Ken!

originalText.text: I was so lucky to find Ken and The Audition Helper. Ever since I have started working with him - my auditions have been more consistent, I have been getting more auditions, more callbacks, and my pieces are coming to life in ways that they haven't before. He is such a fun, caring, and insightful teacher who knows how to get wonderful things out of you and your pieces that you never thought possible. And the fact that you can schedule a session on your time and in your own home is incredible! Don't think twice - sign up with the audition helper today!

originalText.text: For me Ken helped me in my audition monologue to keep it real, to really say it, truly say it. being specific in every sentence with my actions, why do I say it and why I say it. it has not only for this monologue, Iv being applying it for other audition and scripts  the way we work on the monologue, and now I feel more confident because I'm being specific.  iI would encourage you to take a session or multiples sessions with ken, you are really gonna improve in your skills and  notice some of your habits and try to get rid of them.
